![団地](https://globalvoices.org/wp-
content/uploads/2017/03/IMAG0692-800x533.jpg)

“Block No. 4, 2-3-2 Honmachi” (in Tsuruga, Fukui Prefecture). Photo by Nevin
Thompson.

In Japan, there are blogs devoted to documenting [train
interiors](http://ameblo.jp/seventhheaven1992/), [manhole
covers](https://www.tumblr.com/tagged/japanese-manhole) and even
[cake](http://blog.with2.net/rank2252-0.html). So it should come as no
surprise that there is a [Tumblr](http://tamazo2.tumblr.com/) and a blog
devoted to [_danchi_ (団地)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Danchi), the clusters
of utilitarian ferro-concrete public housing projects where so many Japanese
people have lived since the end of World War II.

This danchi blog provides a rare glimpse into how many people live in Japan,
even today.

The term danchi can have negative connotations in Japanese, akin to “the
projects” or “social housing” in English. Formerly speaking, these are all
known as _koei jutaku_ (公営住宅) _,_ or public housing in Japanese.

> Concrete lovers, this blog explores the housing estates of Japan. Also known
> as ‘danchi’<https://t.co/YvZgQsTwCL>
> [pic.twitter.com/vybt7p6bki](https://t.co/vybt7p6bki)
>
> — Present & Correct (@presentcorrect) [March 22,
> 2017](https://twitter.com/presentcorrect/status/844557212576026624)

As discussed on American web forum
[MetaFilter](http://www.metafilter.com/165822/Walking-in-the-Danchi), [Walking
in the Danchi !!](http://tamazo2.tumblr.com/) is a Japanese-language blog
devoted to sharing images of housing estates around Japan. The blog is
frequently updated, and features photos of housing blocks from all over Japan,
including
[Kyoto](http://tamazo2.tumblr.com/post/157074174329/%E6%B4%9B%E8%A5%BF%E5%A2%83%E8%B0%B7%E6%9D%B1%E5%9B%A3%E5%9C%B01979-80%E5%B9%B4-%E4%BA%AC%E9%83%BD%E5%B8%82%E8%A5%BF%E4%BA%AC%E5%8C%BA-2017),
[central
Tokyo](http://tamazo2.tumblr.com/post/158184145100/%E7%94%B0%E7%94%BA%E9%A7%85%E5%89%8D%E3%82%A2%E3%83%91%E3%83%BC%E3%83%881966%E5%B9%B4-%E6%9D%B1%E4%BA%AC%E9%83%BD%E5%8C%BA%E6%B8%AF%E5%8C%BA%E8%8A%9D-2016),
[Osaka](http://tamazo2.tumblr.com/post/158708056151/%E5%A4%A7%E9%98%AA%E5%BA%9C%E5%96%B6%E9%96%80%E7%9C%9F%E4%BD%8F%E5%AE%851967%E5%B9%B4-%E5%A4%A7%E9%98%AA%E5%BA%9C%E9%96%80%E7%9C%9F%E5%B8%82-2017)
and many other parts of Japan. The posts include information about the
specific address of the tower blocks, and when they were built:

[![](https://globalvoices.org/wp-
content/uploads/2017/03/tamachiekimae.png)](http://tamazo2.tumblr.com/post/158102460783/%E7%94%B0%E7%94%BA%E9%A7%85%E5%89%8D%E3%82%A2%E3%83%91%E3%83%BC%E3%83%881966%E5%B9%B4-%E6%9D%B1%E4%BA%AC%E9%83%BD%E5%8C%BA%E6%B8%AF%E5%8C%BA%E8%8A%9D-2016)

Screenshot from Walking in the Danchi !! Tumblr blog.

