Writing for the Japan Times, [Philip
Brasor](https://twitter.com/philipbrasor?lang=en) provides [a useful primer on
public housing in Japan](http://www.japantimes.co.jp/community/2015/04/04/how-
tos/japans-public-housing-system-shelf-life/#.WNRr4zvythE), including
government housing policy since the Second World War, who qualifies for public
housing in Japan, as well as how less government investment in public housing
in recent years, combined with [the rise of precarious work and declining
wages](http://www.nippon.com/en/currents/d00151/) is leading to evermore
[income disparity in Japan](https://www.weforum.org/agenda/2015/03/why-
inequality-is-different-in-japan/).

